Chapter XIV
  See for Ireland, W. Stokes, &ldquo;The Prose Tales in the Rennes Dindsenchas,&rdquo; RC 16 (1895), no. 145: &ldquo;A great whirlpool there is between Ireland and Scotland on the North. It is the meeting of many seas (from NSEW) — it resembles an open caldron which casts the draught down (and) up, and its roaring is heard like far off thunder . . .&rdquo;
